2
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.990
<b>Big News</b>

3
00:00:11.070 --> 00:00:18.000
<b>Pangaea Castle
Mary Geoise</b>

4
00:00:13.580 --> 00:00:16.120
The World Conference,
also known as the Reverie...

5
00:00:16.830 --> 00:00:19.500
is a grand assembly of fifty kings and queens

6
00:00:19.500 --> 00:00:25.760
that represents over 170 countries
affiliated with the World Government.

7
00:00:25.760 --> 00:00:28.760
It is held every four years.

8
00:00:34.970 --> 00:00:38.980
As always, the Reverie concluded
in a state of great confusion

9
00:00:38.980 --> 00:00:42.270
and all the representatives returned home.

10
00:00:43.110 --> 00:00:44.110
Then...

11
00:00:45.900 --> 00:00:48.320
one week later...

12
00:00:49.650 --> 00:00:53.200
Good grief... I'm finally home.

13
00:00:50.280 --> 00:00:53.200
<b>Ryugu Palace, Ryugu Kingdom
Fishman Island</b>

14
00:00:53.200 --> 00:00:58.160
Truly, the surface world is so far above us.

15
00:00:58.540 --> 00:01:02.170
Um, thank you so much for escorting us,

16
00:01:02.170 --> 00:01:04.500
Sir Luffy's grandfather!

17
00:01:04.500 --> 00:01:07.420
It was a pretty long trip, huh, Neptune?

18
00:01:07.760 --> 00:01:09.670
You must be tired!

19
00:01:11.840 --> 00:01:13.760
I'm exhausted.

20
00:01:13.760 --> 00:01:17.220
Garp, stay here with us
and replenish your energy.

21
00:01:17.220 --> 00:01:20.940
Well, maybe I'll have a cup of tea,

22
00:01:20.940 --> 00:01:24.940
but considering the situation,
I can't stay here for long.

23
00:01:26.610 --> 00:01:29.440
The Reverie always triggers big incidents.

24
00:01:30.240 --> 00:01:35.410
When fifty countries gather,
a simple "let's get along" won't suffice.

25
00:01:36.200 --> 00:01:39.160
Each of them has their own internal troubles.

26
00:01:39.580 --> 00:01:43.170
Large and mighty countries
just stare quietly at each other

27
00:01:43.170 --> 00:01:45.500
and let their proxies bicker.

28
00:01:48.340 --> 00:01:52.430
They use resources
and technologies as leverage.

29
00:01:54.800 --> 00:01:59.270
They say that all countries
are on equal footing, but that's just talk.

30
00:01:59.810 --> 00:02:06.110
Wealth, poverty, and religious differences
won't allow them to be equal.

31
00:02:11.780 --> 00:02:16.320
Even if they appear to shake hands and smile,
they'll gladly step on each other's feet.

32
00:02:16.320 --> 00:02:23.080
I wonder how many leaders can speak for both
their citizens and those of other countries.

33
00:02:23.080 --> 00:02:25.420
It's only a roundtable in name.

34
00:02:25.420 --> 00:02:30.210
You're right. Conversations among
the sovereigns were touch and go.

35
00:02:30.210 --> 00:02:36.550
We're no exception, but quarrels between
countries can't be solved so easily.

36
00:02:37.010 --> 00:02:39.220
The further a country's history extends,

37
00:02:39.220 --> 00:02:42.520
the deeper the roots of its conflict will grow.

38
00:02:43.430 --> 00:02:49.190
Even if there is a disagreement,
as long as no blood is spilled, I call it peace.

39
00:02:50.190 --> 00:02:52.780
But what happened this time was pretty bad...

40
00:02:53.320 --> 00:02:58.570
This may be coming a bit late, but there's
one thing I haven't told you about yet.

41
00:02:58.570 --> 00:03:03.750
Right after the Reverie was dismissed
and we set off, an incident occurred,

42
00:03:04.080 --> 00:03:06.500
I received a report while aboard our ship.

43
00:03:07.460 --> 00:03:11.920
We Marines will do our best
to resolve it, but please don't fear

44
00:03:12.340 --> 00:03:15.340
the surface world or us humans!

45
00:03:16.340 --> 00:03:17.840
An incident...?

46
00:03:17.840 --> 00:03:21.600
Garp, what kind of report did you receive?

47
00:03:22.640 --> 00:03:25.600
The incident concerns
the Kingdom of Alabasta.

48
00:03:25.600 --> 00:03:27.560
The Kingdom of Alabasta...

49
00:03:28.900 --> 00:03:30.360
Princess Vivi!

50
00:03:32.400 --> 00:03:35.320
Before all of this transpired...

51
00:03:35.860 --> 00:03:39.620
At the World Economic News,
right after the Reverie was dismissed...

52
00:03:40.240 --> 00:03:43.240
Unbelievable! It's incident after incident!

53
00:03:43.240 --> 00:03:46.120
I can't believe so much happened at once...

54
00:03:46.120 --> 00:03:49.330
Listen up! Find me
the greatest headline yet!

55
00:03:50.460 --> 00:03:53.710
Sir, which one should make the front page?!

56
00:03:54.670 --> 00:03:56.970
Listen! We have a death on our hands!

57
00:03:54.760 --> 00:03:59.840
<b>Editor-in-Chief Morgans
World Economic Newspaper</b>

58
00:03:56.970 --> 00:03:59.840
Big obituaries move papers!

59
00:03:59.840 --> 00:04:00.970
Then, the headli–

60
00:04:00.970 --> 00:04:02.470
No, wait!

61
00:04:02.470 --> 00:04:04.720
The resolution they passed is also good.

62
00:04:04.720 --> 00:04:08.230
But a murder attempt is exciting as well!

63
00:04:08.230 --> 00:04:09.400
That's right!

64
00:04:09.400 --> 00:04:11.270
Okay, let's have two front pages!

65
00:04:11.270 --> 00:04:13.520
The back page will have the same format!

66
00:04:13.520 --> 00:04:14.820
– Okay!
– Okay!

67
00:04:14.820 --> 00:04:16.400
Sir.

68
00:04:16.400 --> 00:04:18.360
Express mail from the government.

69
00:04:19.410 --> 00:04:20.780
A check, huh?

70
00:04:20.780 --> 00:04:23.030
Oh, that's a lot!

71
00:04:23.030 --> 00:04:26.290
I see. It's an order to manipulate information.

72
00:04:26.290 --> 00:04:28.660
But for which affair?

73
00:04:32.130 --> 00:04:35.340
Hushing up this incident?!

74
00:04:35.340 --> 00:04:36.840
No way in hell!

75
00:04:37.380 --> 00:04:39.340
Throw this back in their faces!

76
00:04:40.300 --> 00:04:41.340
Hey, what's wrong?

77
00:04:41.340 --> 00:04:43.390
My, my, my...

78
00:04:46.600 --> 00:04:49.520
Do as you're told, Morgans!

79
00:04:49.520 --> 00:04:50.730
The secret agency,

80
00:04:50.730 --> 00:04:52.150
Cipher Pol?!

81
00:04:52.520 --> 00:04:55.980
You must obey orders
from the World Government.

82
00:04:55.980 --> 00:04:56.860
Don't move!

83
00:05:01.450 --> 00:05:05.870
Never underestimate Big News Morgans!

84
00:05:10.500 --> 00:05:12.630
When did he sneak in?

85
00:05:13.250 --> 00:05:17.130
Sir! Members of Cipher Pol
are government officials!

86
00:05:17.130 --> 00:05:18.260
I know!

87
00:05:18.260 --> 00:05:20.470
It's dangerous to stay here, guys.

88
00:05:20.470 --> 00:05:22.340
Let's fly!

89
00:05:25.970 --> 00:05:28.220
I may be avaricious,

90
00:05:28.220 --> 00:05:31.310
but I am first and foremost a journalist!

91
00:05:31.470 --> 00:05:33.730
I make people dance to the tune of my lies.

92
00:05:33.730 --> 00:05:35.440
I'm a DJ of words!

93
00:05:35.440 --> 00:05:39.400
I decide what to publish!

94
00:05:43.410 --> 00:05:44.940
Mr. Morgans!

95
00:05:45.410 --> 00:05:47.700
You have a call from King Wapol!

96
00:05:47.700 --> 00:05:49.120
King Wapol?

97
00:05:51.040 --> 00:05:52.870
What does he want?

98
00:05:52.870 --> 00:05:56.090
Well, it sounds like he has information to leak.

99
00:05:56.090 --> 00:05:58.170
What?!

100
00:06:08.510 --> 00:06:10.020
What's going on?

101
00:06:10.020 --> 00:06:11.100
A special report?

102
00:06:19.030 --> 00:06:19.940
Don't worry...

103
00:06:20.440 --> 00:06:21.860
It'll be all right.

104
00:06:29.200 --> 00:06:32.540
With the government's failure
to hush up what had happened,

105
00:06:32.540 --> 00:06:37.290
the decisions the leaders made at the Reverie,
as well as the incidents that occurred there,

106
00:06:37.290 --> 00:06:42.090
instantly became known throughout the world
and left many people in shock.

107
00:06:43.550 --> 00:06:44.930
Vayyt!

108
00:06:44.930 --> 00:06:46.340
Vhaat the hell is this?!

109
00:06:49.640 --> 00:06:51.350
This cannot be true!

110
00:06:49.640 --> 00:06:57.060
<b>Revolutionary Army Headquarters
Kamabakka Queendom</b>

111
00:06:51.350 --> 00:06:53.480
It is just a story in the paper, right?

112
00:06:53.480 --> 00:06:57.060
That is just the WEN! Their bird president
must have written nonsense!

113
00:06:57.610 --> 00:06:59.520
I am sure of it!

114
00:07:02.940 --> 00:07:04.820
This is Sabo after all!

115
00:07:04.820 --> 00:07:06.450
It just cannot be...

116
00:07:06.450 --> 00:07:08.660
I do not buy it!

117
00:07:08.660 --> 00:07:09.780
Calm down!

118
00:07:10.410 --> 00:07:13.620
First, we must confirm the facts.

119
00:07:13.620 --> 00:07:16.040
But with all of them out of contact...

120
00:07:17.000 --> 00:07:18.630
how can we confirm?

121
00:07:19.290 --> 00:07:21.000
It's not true, is it?

122
00:07:22.420 --> 00:07:23.800
Sabo...

123
00:07:25.130 --> 00:07:27.800
<b>Royal Escort Ship
Kingdom of Goa</b>

124
00:07:26.590 --> 00:07:27.800
My lady!

125
00:07:27.800 --> 00:07:29.850
He was in Mary Geoise?!

126
00:07:30.300 --> 00:07:32.890
M-My brother?!

127
00:07:33.220 --> 00:07:40.400
<b>Windmill Village
Kingdom of Goa</b>

128
00:07:35.520 --> 00:07:37.430
What happened to Makino?

129
00:07:37.430 --> 00:07:39.230
The bar is closed today.

130
00:07:39.230 --> 00:07:40.400
What?!

131
00:07:40.400 --> 00:07:43.610
So much has happened in the world...

132
00:07:43.610 --> 00:07:45.610
I could use a drink.

133
00:07:48.860 --> 00:07:50.370
Sabo is...

134
00:07:52.830 --> 00:07:56.500
And I had just learned he was still alive...

135
00:07:52.830 --> 00:07:59.040
<b>Mt. Colubo
Kingdom of Goa</b>

136
00:07:57.080 --> 00:07:59.040
Tell me it's not true!

137
00:07:59.040 --> 00:08:04.210
Sabo!

138
00:08:06.760 --> 00:08:09.680
<b>Undersea Prison Impel Down</b>

139
00:08:10.550 --> 00:08:14.430
I never get bored with this world!

140
00:08:15.470 --> 00:08:17.600
It's getting interesting!

141
00:08:24.650 --> 00:08:27.280
Hey, guys!

142
00:08:25.070 --> 00:08:27.280
<b>Beehive
Pirate Island</b>

143
00:08:27.280 --> 00:08:29.030
Let's set sail!

144
00:08:29.030 --> 00:08:31.620
Instead of watching
the Marines snatch it away,

145
00:08:31.620 --> 00:08:34.540
I'll take it for myself!

146
00:08:39.420 --> 00:08:42.330
And now, we return to the present...

147
00:08:47.210 --> 00:08:47.260
<b>The Outskirts 
of Ebisu Town

Wano</b>

